1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,450
If you want love, you give love

2
00:00:02,450 --> 00:00:04,605
and in return you get love.

3
00:00:04,605 --> 00:00:07,339
If you want kindness, you give kindness

4
00:00:07,339 --> 00:00:10,720
and in exchange you earn kindness.

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:12,943
If you want hate, you give hate.

6
00:00:12,943 --> 00:00:14,863
What do you get in return?

7
00:00:14,863 --> 00:00:15,840
Hate, of course.

8
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:20,878
How do the rich become rich?

9
00:00:20,878 --> 00:00:23,060
By hoarding or by giving?

10
00:00:23,060 --> 00:00:23,900
By giving.

11
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,833
Why are the poor so poor?

12
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:30,108
What are they poor at?

13
00:00:30,108 --> 00:00:30,701
Giving.

14
00:00:30,701 --> 00:00:34,214
What are the rich rich at?

15
00:00:34,214 --> 00:00:34,707
Giving.

16
00:00:34,707 --> 00:00:39,420
That's why the rich are rich and the poor
poor.

17
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:44,268
You know, when you begin to understand the
Dhamma,

18
00:00:44,268 --> 00:00:51,883
you will begin to realize everything in
life, everything, like you've never done before.
